title: Liliom (1934)
description:
Two women love the same man in a world of few prospects. In Budapest, Liliom is a "public figure," a rascal who's a carousel barker, loved by the experienced merry-go-round owner and by a young, innocent maid. The maid, Julie, loses her job when she chooses to go out with Liliom; he's fired by his jealous employer for going out with her. The two lovers move in with Julie's aunt; he's emasculated by the unemployment, tempted to crime by a local weasel. She's true to Liliom even in his bad temper, while a stolid widower, a carpenter, makes it clear he would like to marry her. Is there any future on this earth for Julie and Liliom, whose love is passionate, not just ideal?
